Weather in Iceland for May 2025

Snow Forecast ❄️

Snowfall in Iceland during May is quite rare, with fewer than 2 snowy days on average.According to Iceland snow forecast for May 2025, no snow is expected at the beginning of the month.

Temperatures

The forecast for the first days of May 2025 in Iceland predicts temperatures to be around 8 °C, close to the historical average. [...] By the end of May, Iceland sees a significant shift in its weather patterns. The average temperature in Reykjavik rises to around 10°, and the country experiences longer daylight hours, providing more opportunities for outdoor activities and sightseeing.

Additionally, the end of May marks the beginning of the peak tourist season in Iceland, as travelers flock to the country to witness the stunning landscapes and natural attractions in the favorable weather conditions. [...] In general, the average temperature in Iceland at the beginning of May is 7.9 °C. As the month progressed, temperatures tended to noticeably warm up, reaching an average of 10 °C by the end of May.

Rain 🌧️

Iceland experiences heavy rainfall in May, with over 20 rainy days and an average total precipitation 124.1 mm.

messages.content: The weather in Iceland in May is cold, with temperatures between 39°F and 48°F. Rain is expected for roughly half of the month. Snowfall is rare, with fewer than 2 snowy days on average. The average temperature at the beginning of May is 7.9°C, warming up to an average of 10°C by the end of May.
